---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Harmonium Chords | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Learn major, minor, and seventh chords for richer harmonium accompaniment. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Harmonium Chords</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-intermediate capitalize">intermediate</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 30 min · Intermediate</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Harmonium Chords</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Learn major, minor, and seventh chords for richer harmonium accompaniment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Major chord = root + major third + fifth</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Minor chord = root + minor third + fifth</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Play Sa Ga Pa together for Sa major chord</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Chords are more common in bhajan than classical</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Dominant seventh creates tension that resolves to tonic</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>Chords in Indian Music</h2>
      <p>Unlike Western music where chords are central Indian classical music primarily uses single-note melody over a continuous drone. However chords are extremely useful for bhajan accompaniment ghazal playing and when performing with Western instruments. Understanding chords also deepens your overall harmonic awareness as a musician.</p>

      <h2>Building a Major Chord</h2>
      <p>A major chord uses three notes: root plus major third (4 semitones up) plus perfect fifth (7 semitones up). Sa major chord: play Sa plus Ga plus Pa simultaneously using keys A D G together. This bright happy sound works perfectly for upbeat devotional bhajans and auspicious ceremonial music.</p>

      <h2>Building a Minor Chord</h2>
      <p>A minor chord: root plus minor third (3 semitones up) plus perfect fifth (7 semitones up). Sa minor: Sa plus Komal Ga plus Pa using keys A E G together. The minor chord has a more contemplative emotional quality appropriate for emotional bhajans and ragas with a serious or tender mood.</p>

      <h2>Dominant Seventh Chord</h2>
      <p>The dominant seventh chord adds a fourth note: Sa7 equals Sa plus Ga plus Pa plus Komal Ni (A D G U). This chord creates musical tension that naturally wants to resolve back to the tonic chord. Using Sa7 before returning to Sa creates a satisfying arrival feeling — useful for phrase endings in accompaniment.</p>

      <h2>Practical Chord Progressions</h2>
      <p>For simple bhajan accompaniment try: Sa major to Pa major back to Sa major. This I V I progression works for most common bhajans. For more sophisticated ghazal accompaniment try: Sa minor to Komal Re major to Sa minor. Practice strumming these chord changes smoothly until you can transition between them without hesitation or gap.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>